Title: 057: Building Image Datasets and Their Importance in Machine Learning
Description:
In this episode of the SuperDataScience Podcast, I chat with Head of Applied Machine Learning Ryan Compton. You will learn about how a Neural Network Filters NSFW images differently from humans, the different applications of Neural Network Image Filters, why artificial intelligence is used in the world and how it is helping organizations deliver better services; and you will also learn about the 2 Growth Areas in AI - the automation and pushing boundaries.


If you enjoyed this episode, check out show notes, resources, and more at www.superdatascience.com/57
